Chapter 15: Unified Thermodynamic Closure Theorem

Theorem 15.1 (Thermodynamic Closure of Recursive Intelligence). A recursive system governed by the TDF is stable if and only if:

\begin{cases} \dot{\Sigma}_{\text{flux}} \ge \dot{\Sigma}_{\text{gen}} \\ \mathcal{G}(R, S) \ge \mathcal{T}(C, T) \\ \Xi(t) \in K_F \\ \text{Mk} < 1 \end{cases}

Proof. The conditions are necessary and sufficient:

1. Entropy Condition: $\dot{\Sigma}_{\text{flux}} \ge \dot{\Sigma}_{\text{gen}}$ ensures the Second Law is satisfied without internal entropy accumulation.
2. Energy Condition: $\mathcal{G} \ge \mathcal{T}$ ensures the First Law permits sustained operation.
