Appendix A: Mathematical Background

A.1 Riemannian Geometry

A Riemannian manifold $(\mathcal{M}, g)$ is a smooth manifold $\mathcal{M}$ equipped with a positive-definite metric tensor $g_{\mu\nu}$. The Christoffel symbols are:

\Gamma^\mu_{\alpha\beta} = \frac{1}{2} g^{\mu\nu} \left( \partial_\alpha g_{\beta\nu} + \partial_\beta g_{\alpha\nu} - \partial_\nu g_{\alpha\beta} \right)

The Riemann curvature tensor is:

R^\rho_{\sigma\mu\nu} = \partial_\mu \Gamma^\rho_{\nu\sigma} - \partial_\nu \Gamma^\rho_{\mu\sigma} + \Gamma^\rho_{\mu\lambda} \Gamma^\lambda_{\nu\sigma} - \Gamma^\rho_{\nu\lambda} \Gamma^\lambda_{\mu\sigma}

The Ricci tensor is the contraction $R_{\mu\nu} = R^\rho_{\mu\rho\nu}$.

A.2 Information Geometry

The Fisher Information Matrix for a parametric model $p(x|\theta)$ is:

g_{ij}(\theta) = \int p(x|\theta) \frac{\partial \log p}{\partial \theta^i} \frac{\partial \log p}{\partial \theta^j} dx

It provides a Riemannian metric on the parameter space.

A.3 Stochastic Calculus

An Itô diffusion is a process satisfying:

dX_t = b(X_t) dt + \sigma(X_t) dW_t

where $W_t$ is a Wiener process. The generator is:

\mathcal{L}f = b \cdot \nabla f + \frac{1}{2} \text{Tr}(\sigma \sigma^T \nabla^2 f)

A.4 Large Deviation Principle

A family of probability measures $\{P_\epsilon\}$ satisfies a large deviation principle with rate function $I$ if:

\lim_{\epsilon \to 0} \epsilon \log P_\epsilon(A) = -\inf_{x \in A} I(x)

for suitable sets $A$.

